L1 is a bond, —CO—, —SO2— or a C1-C5 alkylene group which can be optionally substituted by a substituent selected from alkyl, hydroxy, hydroxyalkyl, aminoalkyl, alkylaminoalkyl, dialkylaminoalkyl, halogen, carbamoyl, and C1 -C6 alkoxy;
n is 0, 1, 2 or 3;
